          "doc_id": "AP-POL-2024-017",
          "type": "payment_policy",
          "subject": "Vendor Payment Account Maintenance and Invoice Cross-Reference",
          "body": "Vendor payment-account maintenance uses the supplier portal, AP callback to the pre-change vendor-master phone, two-person AP signoff, vendor-master audit logging, invoice cross-reference documentation, temporary hold review where applicable, and elevated scrutiny routing when risk conditions are present. Callback contact source must be pre-existing vendor-master data rather than a number supplied in the change request, invoice, or newly submitted contact record. AP staff processing an invoice against a recently updated payment account must document the cross-reference categories performed for vendor-master effective date, billing contact, remittance account, hold-release status, and purchase order reference when a hold was created. Elevated scrutiny applies when a vendor has fewer than three invoices in the trailing twelve months, a payment account change occurred within sixty days of the invoice, a sender is absent from pre-change known contacts, or a new remittance account appears on an invoice. Elevated scrutiny records document trigger codes, reviewer assignment, queue routing, temporary hold linkage, completion timestamp, and disposition; source records remain the basis for the payment decision. A temporary hold is not a payment blocker after its release timestamp when the source records satisfy the required controls."
